MARKET-BASED RATE TARIFF 1. AVAILABILITY Puget Sound Energy, Inc. ("PSE") makes electric energy and capacity available under this Tariff to any purchaser for resale except as limited in Paragraph 7 below. 2. ANCILLARY SERVICES Seller also makes available to any purchaser the ancillary services listed in this Paragraph. RTO/ISO Specific California: PSE offers Regulation Service, Spinning Reserve Service, and Non- Spinning Reserve Service to the California Independent System Operator Corporation ("CAISO") and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to the CAISO. Third Party Provider Third-party ancillary services: PSE offers Regulation Service, Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service, Energy and Generator Imbalance Service, Operating Reserve-Spinning, Operating Reserve-Supplemental, and Primary Frequency Response Service. Sales will not include the following: (1) sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e., where that entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; and (2) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier. Sales of Operating Reserve-Spinning and Operating Reserve-Supplemental will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except where the Commission has granted authorization. Sales of Regulation Service and Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except at rates not to exceed the buying public utility transmission provider's OATT rate for the same service or where the Commission has granted authorization.
3. APPLICABILITY This Tariff is applicable to all sales of electric energy, capacity, and ancillary services by PSE, which are (a) subject to the jurisdiction of the Commission, and (b) not made pursuant to another tariff on file with the Commission.
4. RATES
All sales under this Tariff shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and PSE.
5. OTHER TERMS AND CONDITIONS
All other terms and conditions of sale shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and PSE.
6. COMPLIANCE WITH COMMISSION REGULATIONS PSE shall comply with the provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning PSE's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes PSE to engage in affiliate sales under this Tariff or otherwise restricts or limits PSE's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning PSE's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff.
7. LIMITATIONS AND EXEMPTIONS REGARDING MARKET-BASED RATE AUTHORITY PSE's tariff excludes market-based sales to customers located within the Puget Sound Energy Balancing Authority Area. See Puget Sound Energy, Inc., 179 FERC 61,182 (2022). This limitation does not apply to sales in the CAISO Energy Imbalance Market.
8. SELLER CATEGORY
Seller is a Category 2 Seller, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a), in the Northwest region, and a Category 1 Seller, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a), in the Central, Northeast, Southwest, Southeast, and Southwest Power Pool regions.
9. EFFECTIVE DATE
This Tariff is effective on such date as set by the Commission.
10. MITIGATED SALES
Sales of energy and capacity are permissible under this tariff in all balancing authority areas where the Seller has been granted market-based rate authority. Sales of energy and capacity under this tariff are also permissible at the metered boundary between the Seller's mitigated balancing authority area and a balancing authority area where the Seller has been granted market-based rate authority provided: (i) legal title of the power sold transfers at the metered boundary of the balancing authority area where the seller has market-based rate authority; and (ii) if the Seller sells at the metered boundary of a mitigated balancing authority area at market-based rates, then neither it nor its affiliates can sell into that mitigated balancing authority area from the outside. Seller must retain, for a period of five years from the date of the sale, all data and information related to the sale that demonstrates compliance with items (i) and (ii) above. Restrictions in this Section do not apply to sales made in the CAISO Energy Imbalance Market.

PUGET SOUND ENERGY, INC. COST-BASED TARIFF
I. DEFINITIONS The following terms shall have the specified meaning when used in this Cost-Based Tariff ("Tariff") or in a Service Agreement: 1. PSE: Puget Sound Energy, Inc., or any successor-in-interest to Puget Sound Energy, Inc. 2. Commission: The Federal Energy Regulatory Commission, or any successor federal agency having jurisdiction over this tariff. 3. Customer: An entity, other than PSE, that executes a Service Agreement under this Tariff. 4. Service Agreement: The initial agreement and any supplements thereto entered into by a Customer and PSE for service under this Tariff. 5. System Incremental Cost: ("SIC") System Incremental Cost means, with respect to a Transaction, all reasonably forecasted incremental generation, power purchase, and other, related costs that PSE would not otherwise incur if such Transaction is not entered into. System Incremental Cost shall include, but not be limited to, costs associated with fuel, labor, variable operation and maintenance, start-up, shut-down, fuel handling, regulatory commission charges, emission allowance and other environmental compliance costs, transmission losses, wheeling charges, any applicable taxes or assessments based on the revenues received or quantities sold under the Transaction, and with respect to capacity and energy purchased from a third party, the total forecasted amount that would be paid for that capacity and energy by PSE. For purchases of energy and capacity by PSE, System Incremental Cost will also include, but not be limited to, regulatory commission charges, emission allowances, transmission losses, wheeling charges and taxes. 6. Tariff: This Cost-Based Tariff, as it may be amended and/or superseded from time to time. 7. Transaction: An individual transaction scheduled pursuant to this Tariff and the applicable Service Agreement. 8. Party: References to a Party shall mean either PSE or the Customer, who collectively shall be referred to as "Parties."
II. AVAILABILITY Service under this Tariff shall be available to Customers for Transactions that have a duration as agreed to by the Parties under the Service Agreement.
III. SALES OF ELECTRIC CAPACITY AND/OR ENERGY PSE and Customers may enter into Transactions under this Tariff from time-to-time. All such Transactions shall be voluntary on the part of PSE and the Customer(s). PSE, at its sole discretion, will determine the amounts of and times that electric capacity and/or energy is to be made available under this Tariff prior to entering into a Transaction.
IV. NON-RATE TERMS AND CONDITIONS All Service Agreements under this Tariff, other than those specified below, shall be governed by the non-rate terms and conditions from the Edison Electric Institute Master Power Purchase & Sale Agreement set forth in Attachment A.
V. RATES 1. A Transaction will be priced at rates established by agreement between Seller and Buyer, provided that the sum of all charges with respect to each Transaction may be up to but shall not exceed the sum of: a) A demand charge, equal to, as appropriate: i. $9,392 /MW-month; ii. $2,167 /MW-week; iii. $434 /MW-day, provided the total demand charge in any week, pursuant to a sale of daily electric power, shall not exceed the weekly rate times the highest amount in megawatts of purchased electric power in any day during such week; or iv. $27 /MWh, provided that the total demand charge in any day, pursuant to a sale of hourly electric power, shall not exceed the daily rate times the highest amount in megawatts of purchased electric power in any hour during such day, and the total demand charges in any week, pursuant to a sale of hourly or daily electric power, shall not exceed the weekly rate times the highest amount in megawatts of purchased electric power in any such week; and b) The System Incremental Cost, forecasted at the time the Transaction is executed, plus 10% of the forecasted System Incremental Cost; and c) The cost of transmission service and any ancillary services purchased by PSE and resold to Customer, as known or forecasted at the time the Transaction is executed.
VI. EXPANSION OF FACILITIES PSE will have no obligation under this Tariff or any Service Agreement executed hereunder to plan its system or modify its facilities in order to provide service hereunder.
VII. OTHER TERMS AND CONDITIONS Except to the extent otherwise specifically agreed to by the Parties, all Transactions under this Tariff shall be governed by the terms and conditions set forth in the Service Agreement.
VIII. SERVICE AGREEMENTS Prior to the commencement of service to a new Customer, PSE and each new Customer will execute a Service Agreement.
